title: Appointments to Human Organ Transplant Board
content_text: All appointments will take effect on February 15, 2018. Details are as follows: Re-appointment of substantive member --------------------------------------------- Dr Gene Tsoi Wai-wang Re-appointment of panel member -------------------------------------- Dr Thomas Yau Chung-cheung Re-appointment of legal advisor ------------------------------------ K&L Gates Appointments of substantive members ------------------------------------------- Mr Nicholas Chan Hiu-fung Dr Josephine Grace Wong Wing-san Appointments of panel members ------------------------------------ Mr Vincent Chin Dr Li Chak-ho Dr Emmy Li Yuen-mei Mr Mui Wai-keung Dr Stanley Tam Kui-fu Mr Wong Tim-wai

Mr Mui Wai-keung Dr Stanley Tam Kui-fu Mr Wong Tim-wai Established under section 3 of the Human Organ Transplant Ordinance, the Board is tasked to consider applications made for the Board's prior written approval to carry out restricted organ removal and/or restricted organ transplant, to receive prescribed information about transplant operations and certificates accompanying imported organs and to perform any other function that the Board is required or permitted to perform under the Ordinance. Under section 3A of the Ordinance, the Board consists of nine substantive members and 14 panel members from the medical, social work, legal and non-medical

nine substantive members and 14 panel members from the medical, social work, legal and non-medical sectors.  The membership of the Board with effect from February 15, 2018, is as follows: Substantive members ------------------------ Miss Ophelia Chan Chiu-ling (Chairman) Miss Sandy Wong Hang-yee (Vice-Chairman) Mr Nicholas Chan Hiu-fung Mr Hui Ching-on Dr Kwok Tin-fook Dr Mark Li Kin-yin Dr Poon Tak-lun Dr Gene Tsoi Wai-wang Dr Josephine Grace Wong Wing-san Panel members ----------------- Dr
